##ubuntu kernel panic /sbin/init libcrypt.so.12 no such file error 

1> boot with same version live cd

2>on live cd os ldd /sbin/init | grep librypt# list files starting with libcrypt

3> mount the hdd check for file

4> ls -ll /lib/x86x64* | grep crypt# check this on live cd 

5> -ll /lib/x86x64* | grep crypt# check this mount path of hdd 

6> ln -s libcrypts0.12.2.20 libcryptsetup.so.1 or

##alternative

7> dpkg -S /lib/x86x64*/libcryptsetup.so.12.2.0 # get the package name

8> chroot hdd mount path

9> apt-get install libcyptrsetup12)pacakge name)

